<subSubSection id="C363FFE7FFBAFFBAFF59D1CAFC9856C4" box="[136,787,2004,2031]" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="8BC6AC6CFFBAFFBAFF59D1CAFC9856C4" blockId="0.[136,1451,2004,2087]" box="[136,787,2004,2031]" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">
<heading id="D08E1B00FFBAFFBAFF59D1CAFC9856C4" bold="true" box="[136,787,2004,2031]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" reason="1">
<emphasis id="B90D707EFFBAFFBAFF59D1CAFC9856C4" bold="true" box="[136,787,2004,2031]" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">
<keyLead id="30880F59FFBAFFBAFF59D1CAFC9856C4" box="[136,787,2004,2031]" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">
<keyStep id="308DB4C9FFBAFFBAFF59D1CAFC9856C4" box="[136,787,2004,2031]" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">
Key to 
<emphasis id="B90D707EFFBAFFBAFF0FD1CAFDA756C5" bold="true" box="[222,556,2004,2031]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">
<taxonomicName id="4C79D7EFFFBAFFBAFF0FD1CAFEE656C5" authorityName="Bunge" authorityYear="1833" box="[222,365,2004,2031]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cucurbitaceae" genus="Thladiantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Thladiantha</taxonomicName>
longipedicellata
</emphasis>
and similar species
</keyStep>
</keyLead>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C363FFE7FFBAFFBBFF59D1EBFA205020" lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="114" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" type="key">
<paragraph id="8BC6AC6CFFBAFFBAFF59D1EBFA20590C" blockId="0.[136,1451,2004,2087]" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">
<keyLead id="30880F59FFBAFFBAFF59D1EBFA20590C" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">
<keyStep id="308DB4C9FFBAFFBAFF59D1EBFA20590C" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">
1a. Male bracts incised ........................................................................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C79D7EFFFBAFFBAFAE4D1EBFA205923" authorityName="Cogniaux" authorityYear="1881" baseAuthorityName="Blume" baseAuthorityYear="1826" box="[1333,1451,2036,2058]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cucurbitaceae" genus="Thladiantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cordifolia">
<emphasis id="B90D707EFFBAFFBAFAE4D1EBFA205923" box="[1333,1451,2036,2058]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">T. cordifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
b. Male bracts dentate.............................................................................................................................................................................2
</keyStep>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC6AC6CFFBBFFBBFF59D681FA205020" blockId="1.[136,1452,159,267]" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">
<keyLead id="30880F59FFBBFFBBFF59D681FA205020" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">
<keyStep id="308DB4C9FFBBFFBBFF59D681FA205020" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">
2a. Vestigial leaves present. Calyx segments linear, margin entire, indistinctly 3-veined, ca. 12 × 
<quantity id="4C810189FFBBFFBBFB9ED681FB02519F" box="[1103,1161,159,181]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
. Male peduncle short, 1–2.5(– 3.5) cm. Male pedicel long, (1.8–) 
<quantity id="4C810189FFBBFFBBFDCAD6A2FDEE51FB" box="[539,613,188,210]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" unit="cm" value="5.0" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="3.0">3–7 cm</quantity>
, 2 to 3 times as long as bracts ............................................................. 
<taxonomicName id="4C79D7EFFFBBFFBBFB26D6A3FA2051FB" authorityName="Gao Xie, Ying Qin &amp; Yan Liu" authorityYear="2022" box="[1271,1451,188,210]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cucurbitaceae" genus="Thladiantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="longipedicellata">
<emphasis id="B90D707EFFBBFFBBFB26D6A3FA2051FB" box="[1271,1451,188,210]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">T. longipedicellata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
b. Vestigial leaves absent. Calyx segments narrowly ovate, apex 3-lobed, distinctly 3-veined, ca. 15 × 
<quantity id="4C810189FFBBFFBBFB5DD6C7FB5551C4" box="[1164,1246,217,239]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" unit="mm" value="5.0" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="4.0">4–6 mm</quantity>
. Male peduncle long, 
<quantity id="4C810189FFBBFFBBFF02D6E8FEA25021" box="[211,297,246,267]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" unit="cm" value="6.5" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="3.0">3–10 cm</quantity>
. Male pedicel short, 
<quantity id="4C810189FFBBFFBBFE20D6EBFDC65021" box="[497,589,245,267]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" unit="cm" value="0.75" valueMax="1.0" valueMin="0.5">0.5–1 cm</quantity>
, nearly as long as bracts ............................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C79D7EFFFBBFFBBFAC5D6E8FA205020" authorityName="Lu &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="1981" box="[1300,1451,245,267]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cucurbitaceae" genus="Thladiantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="grandisepala">
<emphasis id="B90D707EFFBBFFBBFAC5D6E8FA205020" box="[1300,1451,245,267]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">T. grandisepala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyStep>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</key>
